  <body>
    <sec sec-type="intro">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <p>Fused nitrogen-containing heterocycles are structural fragments of many natural compounds and are important for various vital processes. Quinazolinones have been frequently used in medicine because of their wide spectrum of biological activities [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B1-molbank-2009-M589">1</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B2-molbank-2009-M589">2</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B3-molbank-2009-M589">3</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B4-molbank-2009-M589">4</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B5-molbank-2009-M589">5</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B6-molbank-2009-M589">6</xref>].  Different quinazolinone derivatives have been reported for their antibacterial, antifungal, anti-HIV, anthelmintic, CNS depressant and antitubercular activities. Schiff bases have also gained importance in recent days due to their potential biological activities [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B7-molbank-2009-M589">7</xref>]. In this paper, we want to report the synthesis of a novel Schiff base from a quinazolinone.</p>
	  <disp-formula>
